  "output": "## Coverage summary\n\n**No test infrastructure exists.** `package.json` has zero test runner, zero `@testing-library/*`, no `test` script, and there isn't a single `*.test.*`/`*.spec.*` file in the project. Every gap below is really \"0% coverage,\" not \"partial.\"\n\nVite is already the build tool, so **Vitest** is the lazy choice (shares Vite's config/transform pipeline, no separate bundler to configure) — skipped Jest, add only if a hard requirement forces it later.\n\n```jsonc\n// package.json — add\n\"devDependencies\": {\n  \"vitest\": \"^2.0.0\",\n  \"jsdom\": \"^25.0.0\",\n  \"@testing-library/react\": \"^16.0.0\"\n},\n\"scripts\": {\n  \"test\": \"vitest\"\n}\n```\n```ts\n// vite.config.ts — add\ntest: { environment: 'jsdom' }\n```\n\n---\n\n## 1. `lenisStore.ts` — untested entirely\n\nFunctions: `set`, `scrollTo`, `stop`, `start`.\n\n**Gaps:**\n- `scrollTo`/`stop`/`start` called before any `set()` — relies on `?.` to no-op silently. Never verified.\n- `scrollTo` accepts `string | number | HTMLElement` — only the union type checks this, no runtime test per variant.\n- Easing function passed to `scrollTo` is a real algorithm (`1.001 - 2^(-10t)` clamped to 1) — never verified as a pure function.\n- `set(null)` after a previous `set(instance)` (the exact sequence `useLenis`'s cleanup does) — never verified it actually detaches.\n\n```ts\n// src/cinematic/lenisStore.test.ts\nimport { describe, it, expect, vi, beforeEach } from 'vitest'\nimport { lenisStore } from './lenisStore'\n\ndescribe('lenisStore', () => {\n  beforeEach(() => lenisStore.set(null))\n\n  it('no-ops scrollTo/stop/start when no instance is set', () => {\n    expect(() => lenisStore.scrollTo('#foo')).not.toThrow()\n    expect(() => lenisStore.stop()).not.toThrow()\n    expect(() => lenisStore.start()).not.toThrow()\n  })\n\n  it('forwards scrollTo to the active instance with duration/easing', () => {\n    const scrollTo = vi.fn()\n    lenisStore.set({ scrollTo, stop: vi.fn(), start: vi.fn() } as any)\n    lenisStore.scrollTo('#section')\n    expect(scrollTo).toHaveBeenCalledWith('#section', expect.objectContaining({ duration: 1.4 }))\n  })\n\n  it.each(['#id', 500, document.createElement('div')])(\n    'accepts target type %p',\n    (target) => {\n      const scrollTo = vi.fn()\n      lenisStore.set({ scrollTo, stop: vi.fn(), start: vi.fn() } as any)\n      lenisStore.scrollTo(target as any)\n      expect(scrollTo).toHaveBeenCalled()\n    },\n  )\n\n  it('stops forwarding once set(null) is called', () => {\n    const stop = vi.fn()\n    lenisStore.set({ scrollTo: vi.fn(), stop, start: vi.fn() } as any)\n    lenisStore.set(null)\n    lenisStore.stop()\n    expect(stop).not.toHaveBeenCalled()\n  })\n})\n```\n\n---\n\n## 2. `scrollTimelines.ts` — `buildCameraTimeline` untested\n\n**Gaps:**\n- No test that the returned timeline is actually a `gsap.timeline` wired to the given `spacer` via `ScrollTrigger` (`start`, `end`, `scrub`).\n- No test of initial `gsap.set` state (landscape scale 1, haze alpha 0, train alpha 1) — regressions here would silently break the opening frame.\n- No test of tween end-state values (`landscape` scale 1.9, `train` scale 6, `train` autoAlpha → 0) — these are the actual visual contract.\n- No test for missing/duplicate refs (e.g., same element passed for two layers) — function has no guard, will silently double-animate.\n\n```ts\n// src/cinematic/scrollTimelines.test.ts\nimport { describe, it, expect, beforeEach } from 'vitest'\nimport gsap from 'gsap'\nimport { buildCameraTimeline, type CameraRefs } from './scrollTimelines'\n\nfunction makeRefs(): CameraRefs {\n  return {\n    spacer: document.createElement('div'),\n    landscape: document.createElement('div'),\n    haze: document.createElement('div'),\n    train: document.createElement('div'),\n  }\n}\n\ndescribe('buildCameraTimeline', () => {\n  let refs: CameraRefs\n  beforeEach(() => { refs = makeRefs() })\n\n  it('sets initial state before animating', () => {\n    buildCameraTimeline(refs)\n    expect(gsap.getProperty(refs.landscape, 'scale')).toBe(1)\n    expect(gsap.getProperty(refs.haze, 'autoAlpha')).toBe(0)\n    expect(gsap.getProperty(refs.train, 'autoAlpha')).toBe(1)\n  })\n\n  it('drives landscape to scale 1.9 and train to scale 6 by timeline end', () => {\n    const tl = buildCameraTimeline(refs)\n    tl.progress(1)\n    expect(gsap.getProperty(refs.landscape, 'scale')).toBeCloseTo(1.9)\n    expect(gsap.getProperty(refs.train, 'scale')).toBeCloseTo(6)\n  })\n\n  it('fades train out only near the end of the scrub', () => {\n    const tl = buildCameraTimeline(refs)\n    tl.progress(0.5)\n    expect(gsap.getProperty(refs.train, 'autoAlpha')).toBe(1)\n    tl.progress(1)\n    expect(gsap.getProperty(refs.train, 'autoAlpha')).toBeCloseTo(0)\n  })\n\n  it('scrubs ScrollTrigger against the spacer element', () => {\n    const tl = buildCameraTimeline(refs)\n    const st = tl.scrollTrigger\n    expect(st?.trigger).toBe(refs.spacer)\n    expect(st?.vars.start).toBe('top top')\n    expect(st?.vars.end).toBe('bottom bottom')\n  })\n})\n```\n\n---\n\n## 3. `useLenis.ts` — hook untested\n\n**Gaps:**\n- Mount → `lenisStore.set` called with a live instance; unmount → called with `null`. Never verified.\n- `gsap.ticker.add`/`remove` called with the *same* function reference (a common bug: passing a new closure to `remove` silently leaks the ticker callback forever). Never verified.\n- `lenis.on('scroll', ScrollTrigger.update)` wiring never verified.\n- Effect has `[]` deps — no test confirms it only runs once even under React 18 StrictMode double-invoke (mount→unmount→mount), which is exactly where ticker-leak bugs hide.\n- `lenis.destroy()` actually called on unmount — never verified.\n\n```tsx\n// src/cinematic/useLenis.test.tsx\nimport { describe, it, expect, vi, afterEach } from 'vitest'\nimport { renderHook } from '@testing-library/react'\nimport gsap from 'gsap'\nimport Lenis from 'lenis'\nimport { useLenis } from './useLenis'\nimport { lenisStore } from './lenisStore'\n\nvi.mock('lenis')\n\ndescribe('useLenis', () => {\n  afterEach(() => vi.restoreAllMocks())\n\n  it('registers the instance in lenisStore on mount, clears it on unmount', () => {\n    const setSpy = vi.spyOn(lenisStore, 'set')\n    const { unmount } = renderHook(() => useLenis())\n    expect(setSpy).toHaveBeenCalledWith(expect.any(Lenis))\n    unmount()\n    expect(setSpy).toHaveBeenLastCalledWith(null)\n  })\n\n  it('adds and removes the exact same raf callback from gsap.ticker', () => {\n    const addSpy = vi.spyOn(gsap.ticker, 'add')\n    const removeSpy = vi.spyOn(gsap.ticker, 'remove')\n    const { unmount } = renderHook(() => useLenis())\n    const registered = addSpy.mock.calls[0][0]\n    unmount()\n    expect(removeSpy).toHaveBeenCalledWith(registered)\n  })\n\n  it('destroys the lenis instance on unmount', () => {\n    const { result, unmount } = renderHook(() => useLenis())\n    const instance = result.current.current!\n    const destroySpy = vi.spyOn(instance, 'destroy')\n    unmount()\n    expect(destroySpy).toHaveBeenCalled()\n  })\n\n  it('survives a StrictMode-style mount/unmount/mount without leaking ticker callbacks', () => {\n    const addSpy = vi.spyOn(gsap.ticker, 'add')\n    const { unmount } = renderHook(() => useLenis())\n    unmount()\n    renderHook(() => useLenis())\n    expect(addSpy).toHaveBeenCalledTimes(2) // one per real mount, none orphaned\n  })\n})\n```\n\n---\n\n## 4. `useMouseParallax.ts` — hook untested (largest gap — most branching logic in the set)\n\n**Gaps:**\n- Early-return branches never tested: `landscapeRef.current`/`trainRef.current` null, `prefers-reduced-motion: reduce`, `pointer: fine` false (touch devices) — three distinct skip paths, three separate bugs waiting.\n- No test that listeners are actually attached only when both guards pass.\n- No test of the coordinate math: cursor in each corner should clamp to ±1 and drive `x`/`y`/`rotationX`/`rotationY` in the documented directions (background moves opposite cursor, less than foreground; rotation tilts *toward* cursor).\n- No test of clamping when `clientX`/`clientY` fall outside the viewport (edge case worth locking down since it feeds a `gsap.utils.clamp`).\n- `pointerleave` (mouseleave) resets all six channels to 0 — untested.\n- Cleanup: listeners removed, tweens killed, transforms reset to 0 on unmount — untested. A miss here is exactly the kind of bug that leaves a stale rotated frame after route change.\n\n```tsx\n// src/cinematic/useMouseParallax.test.tsx\nimport { describe, it, expect, vi, beforeEach } from 'vitest'\nimport { renderHook } from '@testing-library/react'\nimport gsap from 'gsap'\nimport { useMouseParallax } from './useMouseParallax'\n\nfunction matchMediaMock(overrides: Record<string, boolean>) {\n  return (query: string) => ({\n    matches: overrides[query] ?? false,\n    media: query,\n    addEventListener: vi.fn(),\n    removeEventListener: vi.fn(),\n  })\n}\n\nfunction setup(mediaOverrides: Record<string, boolean> = {}) {\n  window.matchMedia = vi.fn(matchMediaMock(mediaOverrides)) as any\n  const landscape = document.createElement('div')\n  const train = document.createElement('div')\n  return { landscape, train }\n}\n\ndescribe('useMouseParallax', () => {\n  beforeEach(() => vi.restoreAllMocks())\n\n  it('skips entirely when refs are null', () => {\n    setup()\n    const addSpy = vi.spyOn(window, 'addEventListener')\n    renderHook(() => useMouseParallax({ current: null }, { current: null }))\n    expect(addSpy).not.toHaveBeenCalledWith('pointermove', expect.any(Function), expect.anything())\n  })\n\n  it('skips when prefers-reduced-motion is set', () => {\n    const { landscape, train } = setup({ '(prefers-reduced-motion: reduce)': true })\n    const addSpy = vi.spyOn(window, 'addEventListener')\n    renderHook(() => useMouseParallax({ current: landscape }, { current: train }))\n    expect(addSpy).not.toHaveBeenCalledWith('pointermove', expect.any(Function), expect.anything())\n  })\n\n  it('skips on coarse/touch pointers', () => {\n    const { landscape, train } = setup({ '(pointer: fine)': false })\n    const addSpy = vi.spyOn(window, 'addEventListener')\n    renderHook(() => useMouseParallax({ current: landscape }, { current: train }))\n    expect(addSpy).not.toHaveBeenCalledWith('pointermove', expect.any(Function), expect.anything())\n  })\n\n  it('drives background opposite and foreground further on corner pointermove', () => {\n    const { landscape, train } = setup({ '(pointer: fine)': true })\n    renderHook(() => useMouseParallax({ current: landscape }, { current: train }))\n    window.dispatchEvent(new PointerEvent('pointermove', { clientX: window.innerWidth, clientY: window.innerHeight / 2 }))\n    gsap.ticker.tick() // flush quickTo\n    expect(gsap.getProperty(landscape, 'x')).toBeLessThan(0)\n    expect(gsap.getProperty(train, 'x')).toBeLessThan(gsap.getProperty(landscape, 'x') as number) // FG moves further\n  })\n\n  it('resets all channels to 0 on mouseleave', () => {\n    const { landscape, train } = setup({ '(pointer: fine)': true })\n    renderHook(() => useMouseParallax({ current: landscape }, { current: train }))\n    window.dispatchEvent(new PointerEvent('pointermove', { clientX: 0, clientY: 0 }))\n    document.documentElement.dispatchEvent(new MouseEvent('mouseleave'))\n    gsap.ticker.tick()\n    expect(gsap.getProperty(landscape, 'x')).toBe(0)\n    expect(gsap.getProperty(train, 'rotationY' as any)).toBeUndefined() // train never gets rotation\n  })\n\n  it('removes listeners and resets transforms on unmount', () => {\n    const { landscape, train } = setup({ '(pointer: fine)': true })\n    const removeSpy = vi.spyOn(window, 'removeEventListener')\n    const { unmount } = renderHook(() => useMouseParallax({ current: landscape }, { current: train }))\n    unmount()\n    expect(removeSpy).toHaveBeenCalledWith('pointermove', expect.any(Function))\n    expect(gsap.getProperty(landscape, 'rotationX')).toBe(0)\n  })\n})\n```\n\n---\n\n## 5. `contactRevealEvent.ts` — trivial, no test needed\n\nJust a string constant export. YAGNI — a test here would just re-assert the string literal.\n\n---\n\n## Integration gaps (cross-module, none exist today)\n\n1. **`useLenis` + `lenisStore` + a consumer calling `lenisStore.scrollTo`** — no test proves that a `scrollTo` call issued from outside the hook (e.g. a nav link) actually reaches the *currently mounted* Lenis instance, including across an unmount/remount cycle.\n2. **`useLenis` + `scrollTrigger` from `buildCameraTimeline`** — no test that `lenis.on('scroll', ScrollTrigger.update)` actually causes a scrubbed timeline built via `buildCameraTimeline` to advance on a simulated Lenis scroll event.\n3. **`CONTACT_REVEALED` event** — dispatched by `WorkSection` (not shown), consumed by `ContactSection` (not shown). No test that the event actually fires once and that a listener attached before dispatch receives it. Worth a skeleton once those components are in view:\n\n```ts\n// contactRevealEvent.integration.test.ts\nimport { describe, it, expect, vi } from 'vitest'\nimport { CONTACT_REVEALED } from './contactRevealEvent'\n\nit('fires exactly once and is observable by a listener', () => {\n  const handler = vi.fn()\n  window.addEventListener(CONTACT_REVEALED, handler)\n  window.dispatchEvent(new Event(CONTACT_REVEALED))\n  expect(handler).toHaveBeenCalledTimes(1)\n})\n```\n\n---\n\n## Priority order\n\n1. Install Vitest + jsdom + Testing Library (blocks everything).\n2. `useMouseParallax` — most branches, most likely to silently regress (three skip conditions).\n3. `useLenis` — ticker leak / destroy-on-unmount is the highest-blast-radius bug class (global scroll breaks site-wide).\n4. `lenisStore` — cheap, pure, do it alongside `useLenis`.\n5. `scrollTimelines` — pin down the visual contract (scale/opacity end-values) so it survives a GSAP upgrade.\n6. Integration tests — after the units above exist, since they mock the same seams.\n",
