        "title": "4. `useMouseParallax.ts` — hook untested (largest gap — most branching logic in the set)",
        "content": "\n**Gaps:**\n- Early-return branches never tested: `landscapeRef.current`/`trainRef.current` null, `prefers-reduced-motion: reduce`, `pointer: fine` false (touch devices) — three distinct skip paths, three separate bugs waiting.\n- No test that listeners are actually attached only when both guards pass.\n- No test of the coordinate math: cursor in each corner should clamp to ±1 and drive `x`/`y`/`rotationX`/`rotationY` in the documented directions (background moves opposite cursor, less than foreground; rotation tilts *toward* cursor).\n- No test of clamping when `clientX`/`clientY` fall outside the viewport (edge case worth locking down since it feeds a `gsap.utils.clamp`).\n- `pointerleave` (mouseleave) resets all six channels to 0 — untested.\n- Cleanup: listeners removed, tweens killed, transforms reset to 0 on unmount — untested. A miss here is exactly the kind of bug that leaves a stale rotated frame after route change.\n\n```tsx\n// src/cinematic/useMouseParallax.test.tsx\nimport { describe, it, expect, vi, beforeEach } from 'vitest'\nimport { renderHook } from '@testing-library/react'\nimport gsap from 'gsap'\nimport { useMouseParallax } from './useMouseParallax'\n\nfunction matchMediaMock(overrides: Record<string, boolean>) {\n  return (query: string) => ({\n    matches: overrides[query] ?? false,\n    media: query,\n    addEventListener: vi.fn(),\n    removeEventListener: vi.fn(),\n  })\n}\n\nfunction setup(mediaOverrides: Record<string, boolean> = {}) {\n  window.matchMedia = vi.fn(matchMediaMock(mediaOverrides)) as any\n  const landscape = document.createElement('div')\n  const train = document.createElement('div')\n  return { landscape, train }\n}\n\ndescribe('useMouseParallax', () => {\n  beforeEach(() => vi.restoreAllMocks())\n\n  it('skips entirely when refs are null', () => {\n    setup()\n    const addSpy = vi.spyOn(window, 'addEventListener')\n    renderHook(() => useMouseParallax({ current: null }, { current: null }))\n    expect(addSpy).not.toHaveBeenCalledWith('pointermove', expect.any(Function), expect.anything())\n  })\n\n  it('skips when prefers-reduced-motion is set', () => {\n    const { landscape, train } = setup({ '(prefers-reduced-motion: reduce)': true })\n    const addSpy = vi.spyOn(window, 'addEventListener')\n    renderHook(() => useMouseParallax({ current: landscape }, { current: train }))\n    expect(addSpy).not.toHaveBeenCalledWith('pointermove', expect.any(Function), expect.anything())\n  })\n\n  it('skips on coarse/touch pointers', () => {\n    const { landscape, train } = setup({ '(pointer: fine)': false })\n    const addSpy = vi.spyOn(window, 'addEventListener')\n    renderHook(() => useMouseParallax({ current: landscape }, { current: train }))\n    expect(addSpy).not.toHaveBeenCalledWith('pointermove', expect.any(Function), expect.anything())\n  })\n\n  it('drives background opposite and foreground further on corner pointermove', () => {\n    const { landscape, train } = setup({ '(pointer: fine)': true })\n    renderHook(() => useMouseParallax({ current: landscape }, { current: train }))\n    window.dispatchEvent(new PointerEvent('pointermove', { clientX: window.innerWidth, clientY: window.innerHeight / 2 }))\n    gsap.ticker.tick() // flush quickTo\n    expect(gsap.getProperty(landscape, 'x')).toBeLessThan(0)\n    expect(gsap.getProperty(train, 'x')).toBeLessThan(gsap.getProperty(landscape, 'x') as number) // FG moves further\n  })\n\n  it('resets all channels to 0 on mouseleave', () => {\n    const { landscape, train } = setup({ '(pointer: fine)': true })\n    renderHook(() => useMouseParallax({ current: landscape }, { current: train }))\n    window.dispatchEvent(new PointerEvent('pointermove', { clientX: 0, clientY: 0 }))\n    document.documentElement.dispatchEvent(new MouseEvent('mouseleave'))\n    gsap.ticker.tick()\n    expect(gsap.getProperty(landscape, 'x')).toBe(0)\n    expect(gsap.getProperty(train, 'rotationY' as any)).toBeUndefined() // train never gets rotation\n  })\n\n  it('removes listeners and resets transforms on unmount', () => {\n    const { landscape, train } = setup({ '(pointer: fine)': true })\n    const removeSpy = vi.spyOn(window, 'removeEventListener')\n    const { unmount } = renderHook(() => useMouseParallax({ current: landscape }, { current: train }))\n    unmount()\n    expect(removeSpy).toHaveBeenCalledWith('pointermove', expect.any(Function))\n    expect(gsap.getProperty(landscape, 'rotationX')).toBe(0)\n  })\n})\n```\n\n---\n\n",
        "level": 2
      },
      {
        "title": "5. `contactRevealEvent.ts` — trivial, no test needed",
        "content": "\nJust a string constant export. YAGNI — a test here would just re-assert the string literal.\n\n---\n\n",
        "level": 2
      },
      {
        "title": "Integration gaps (cross-module, none exist today)",
        "content": "\n1. **`useLenis` + `lenisStore` + a consumer calling `lenisStore.scrollTo`** — no test proves that a `scrollTo` call issued from outside the hook (e.g. a nav link) actually reaches the *currently mounted* Lenis instance, including across an unmount/remount cycle.\n2. **`useLenis` + `scrollTrigger` from `buildCameraTimeline`** — no test that `lenis.on('scroll', ScrollTrigger.update)` actually causes a scrubbed timeline built via `buildCameraTimeline` to advance on a simulated Lenis scroll event.\n3. **`CONTACT_REVEALED` event** — dispatched by `WorkSection` (not shown), consumed by `ContactSection` (not shown). No test that the event actually fires once and that a listener attached before dispatch receives it. Worth a skeleton once those components are in view:\n\n```ts\n// contactRevealEvent.integration.test.ts\nimport { describe, it, expect, vi } from 'vitest'\nimport { CONTACT_REVEALED } from './contactRevealEvent'\n\nit('fires exactly once and is observable by a listener', () => {\n  const handler = vi.fn()\n  window.addEventListener(CONTACT_REVEALED, handler)\n  window.dispatchEvent(new Event(CONTACT_REVEALED))\n  expect(handler).toHaveBeenCalledTimes(1)\n})\n```\n\n---\n\n",
        "level": 2
      },
      {
        "title": "Priority order",
        "content": "1. Install Vitest + jsdom + Testing Library (blocks everything).\n2. `useMouseParallax` — most branches, most likely to silently regress (three skip conditions).\n3. `useLenis` — ticker leak / destroy-on-unmount is the highest-blast-radius bug class (global scroll breaks site-wide).\n4. `lenisStore` — cheap, pure, do it alongside `useLenis`.\n5. `scrollTimelines` — pin down the visual contract (scale/opacity end-values) so it survives a GSAP upgrade.\n6. Integration tests — after the units above exist, since they mock the same seams.",
        "level": 2
      }
    ],
